<br>
&quot;I was recently introduced to this board game as I babysat my sisters within Kelethin.  They wished to play at it almost every evening!  Since returning to my adventures, I have found a great deal of others have also heard of such a game!<br>
<br>
I rushed back to Kelethin to purchase a playing board of my own (which cost a great deal of platinum!) and her I am!  This past evening Myself, along with a number of friends from the family of Saga, had a grand time playing within a board that one Norr had drawn up and created on his own!  After the game finished, Kanina and myself decided to continue again... except my board began to crumble and fall apart (rest assured that I have since repaired my gaming board, and it looks as perfect and new as the afternoon on which I had purchased it.<br>
<br>
I set this board up this evening in this very spot as an invitation to any who would once again care to play.  I fear I am not are artistic nor creative as Norr, and will not currently be drawing up my own board, so I will use the normal playing board.  Such is all and well, considering I have yet to fully understand all of the strange rules.  Considering my busy day with the household chores this evening, I will be setting up the board to be played at ten in the evening by the standard time of EASTERN Kelethin. =)  Kanina has expressed interest in once again playing, and I have informed her with a personal letter of these such plans.  I shall do the same for Pryce.<br>
<br>
I shall write my own name of       &quot;Ayrielle&quot;        upon the board, and I will use the rules of        Role Play         so when you look to play, do search there.  =)  I will open the game to a great deal of people, in case many wish to come, and there shall be no secretly spoken password to come and play.  Perhaps a stranger will stumble upon us and all shall find a new friend.<br>
<br>
All are invited to come.  Please do bring your own playing figurine or quickly fashion a new one, as I only have my own (and she has a wild mind of her own.  I am only able to move her about the board, and she will not listen to a great deal of my orders anyway!  I point to one square, and she runs to another!  She speaks her mind as she sees fit, regardless of my attempts to hush her!  And best not ask about Pavel!)<br>
<br>
*You see that the letter is signed in a flourish of beautiful letters, that, after studing for a moment, can be read as 'Ayrielle'*  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uayrielle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ayrielle</A> at: 6/27/02 2:30:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uminuetthetalechaser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minuet the Talechaser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sister</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#660000>(6/27/02 7:47:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=544.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: *pulls out her game board for never ending nights of win</span><hr size=1> Maybe by Friday, Ayrielle.<br>
