<br>
&quot;All involved have my deepest apoligies, as this evening's planned game seems to have gone... poorly.  I myself had set up the board incorrectly no fewer than twice and have learned two valuable lessons for all to note in the future.<br>
<br>
There is a figureine upon the playing board by the name of Aribeth who talks far too much.  I should have done well to started the game upon the second block instead of the first.<br>
<br>
Leaving the game open to strangers did not have the affect for which I had planned, and we soon found several others pushing their way onto our board and throwing several of the figureines to the floor.  As much as it would depress myself to do such, I believe it may be difficult to have fun without locking the door to the hall behind ourselves so as to keep strangers out.<br>
<br>
I had also set up this evening's game rather hastily.  It was only meant to be a small game involving myself and Kanina's figureine with any others who wished to come along.  If such a board is to be set up in the future, I would give notice ahead of time.&quot;<br>
<br>
=)<br>
